        <div2>
          <head>
            <title type="main"><hi rend="i">MLA VOLUME ON BLAKE’S</hi> SONGS</title>
          </head>
          <p>Robert F. Gleckner and Mark L. Greenberg are preparing a volume in the MLA series, Approaches to
Teaching Masterpieces of World Literature, devoted to Blake’s <hi rend="i">Songs.</hi> Questionnaires
concerning teaching strategies, editions used in class, and appropriate ancillary materials are being sent to
all subscribers to <hi rend="i">Blake.</hi> Based in part upon responses to these questionnaires, we will
invite brief essays for the volume. If you are not a subscriber or have not received a questionnaire by 1
April and wish to participate in any way, please write to Gleckner (at Duke University) or to Greenberg (at
Drexel University).</p>
        </div2>
      </div1>
